parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, resulting in a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies without warning
the ignition switch is hot to the touch
smoke or fire is coming from the ignition switch area
the vehicle is difficult to start or will not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: A burning smell is coming from the vehicle
smoke or fire is coming from the electrical system
the horn buttons shrink in cold weather
the key is hot to the touch when removing it from the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The alternator is burning or smoking
the insulation on the wire is burning
the connector shows signs of burned and melted insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioner refuses to work until the vehicle has been running for a certain amount of time
the air conditioner has been recharged and checked multiple times
the climate control temperature sensor has been replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause the driver to lose control, resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the front tires are on fire
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without pressing the accelerator pedal
making it difficult to stop or control the vehicle. The cruise control may fail to disengage
and the vehicle may surge or accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter switch can cause intermittent stalling, failure to start, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents, property damage, and safety hazards.
symptoms: The starter switch gets very warm or hot
burned contacts
deformed switch
melted harness connector
turn signals and A/C fan motor do not work
erroneous engine warning and low oil warning lights
failure to start
intermittent stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause intermittent stalling, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Intermittent stalling
engine failure
ignition module replacement does not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Block Heater Cord Installation Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper installation of the engine block heater cord can cause engine fires, resulting in property damage and safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine fire
major property damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause accidents, loss of control, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause engine damage, decreased performance, and potentially lead to safety hazards.
symptoms: Catalytic converter failure
breakdown of the lining
need for replacement.
